cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.AI 

This paper deals with natural language processing methods for medical auto-coding, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a method that uses a model to estimate the conditional probability of code co-occurrence, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG). The method also involves modifying the confidence scores of codes, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper deals with medical data, which involves issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the proposed method involves using an iterative algorithm to modify the output of an existing auto-coder, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
